What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this course to students who are willing to expand their academic perspectives. At first, this course was challenging because the readings were vastly different from high school-level works. However, this is a great introduction to philosophy.

I would definitely recommend this course to any Yale freshman. The class is very engaging, relying heavily on class participation, and every reading is very interesting!I feel that this course has prepared me very well for all of my future classes at Yale.
Yes - this course was one of the best I have taken at Yale.
I would totally recommend the course. I know this is clich, but it really did change the way I think.
A really good class, a time for low-stress, open ended mental exercise. I recommend it.
